Here.

18
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:34,360
Come on.

19
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:36,080
Take it.

20
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:43,570
Are you alright?

21
00:02:50,590 --> 00:02:51,130
Wai.

22
00:02:51,740 --> 00:02:52,450
It seems

23
00:02:52,900 --> 00:02:53,980
that the bullet is still inside you.

24
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:56,220
How did you get shot?

25
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:57,850
And

26
00:02:58,180 --> 00:02:59,660
what's in the car outside?

27
00:03:01,710 --> 00:03:03,100
A batch of arms.

28
00:03:03,540 --> 00:03:05,060
I stole them for Chi Cheung-wing.

29
00:03:07,380 --> 00:03:09,130
But I haven't told him
how to give them to him yet.

30
00:03:10,100 --> 00:03:11,340
You actually helped him steal that?

31
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:12,660
That's way too risky.

32
00:03:13,660 --> 00:03:15,260
You've got a wife and kids at home.

33
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:19,410
That's exactly why I did it,
for my wife and kids.

34
00:03:20,460 --> 00:03:21,940
Now things have turned out like this,

35
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:25,170
you don't think
you're off the hook, do you?

36
00:03:25,540 --> 00:03:26,610
Why would I think that?

37
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,290
If I were that kind of guy,

38
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:29,660
you wouldn't have come to me
in the first place.

39
00:03:34,580 --> 00:03:35,690
Let's dress your wound first.

40
00:03:40,820 --> 00:03:41,300
Come on.

41
00:03:41,820 --> 00:03:42,420
Be careful.

42
00:03:46,180 --> 00:03:46,780
Yat-wai,

43
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:48,500
I've got something
to take care of today,

44
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:49,780
so I can't drive you to school.

45
00:03:49,780 --> 00:03:50,730
You want me to call a cab for you?

46
00:03:50,940 --> 00:03:52,020
No, it's okay. I'll take the bus.

47
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,340
Whose car is this?

48
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:54,460
It's a friend's.

49
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:55,220
They'll drive it away soon.

50
00:03:55,660 --> 00:03:56,780
You're getting late. Chop chop.

51
00:04:17,220 --> 00:04:17,580
Wai.

52
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:19,220
Wai.

53
00:04:26,380 --> 00:04:27,100
Oh, gosh.

54
00:04:27,940 --> 00:04:28,900
You're burning.

55
00:04:48,420 --> 00:04:49,020
Hey.

56
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:51,250
I don't care who you are.

57
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:53,020
Tell Cho Wai-yi

58
00:04:53,630 --> 00:04:54,610
he can't hide forever.

59
00:05:05,780 --> 00:05:06,420
Wai.

60
00:05:08,060 --> 00:05:08,700
Wai.

61
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:12,540
Are you alright?

62
00:05:12,780 --> 00:05:13,490
How are you holding up?

63
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:18,900
Yat-wai.

64
00:05:23,460 --> 00:05:24,730
You guys go grab some food first.

65
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:30,180
Grandma,

66
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:31,580
did something go wrong?

67
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:33,540
No.

68
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:36,380
I just want to ask you something.

69
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:37,500
Come here.

70
00:05:37,660 --> 00:05:38,170
Sit down.

71
00:05:44,380 --> 00:05:45,700
Someone gave you a call just now.

72
00:06:16,260 --> 00:06:16,930
Hey.

73
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:18,930
This is Cho Wai-yi.

74
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:21,940
You're not dead. That means you got it?

75
00:06:22,580 --> 00:06:23,900
I'll hand them over to you today.

76
00:06:24,780 --> 00:06:26,170
Why not yesterday?

77
00:06:27,860 --> 00:06:29,250
With that drama last night,

78
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:30,370
do you expect me to wander around?

79
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:31,780
Am I that stupid?

80
00:06:33,820 --> 00:06:35,020
I swear on my son.

81
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:38,410
Everything's in my hands.

82
00:06:40,740 --> 00:06:42,100
You have two hours.

83
00:06:42,140 --> 00:06:43,660
Get them here right now.

84
00:06:44,660 --> 00:06:45,660
Chi Cheung-wing,

85
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:50,060
don't you think you owe me the truth?

86
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,850
I'm standing in front of the gods.

87
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:58,290
I promise you a lifetime of safety
for your wife and your kids.

88
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:01,050
I mean what I say.

89
00:07:01,310 --> 00:07:01,930
OK.

90
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:03,860
That's enough.

91
00:07:11,220 --> 00:07:11,620
Wai.

92
00:07:12,540 --> 00:07:13,620
How can you go like this?

93
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:18,170
He's threatening me with my sons' lives.

94
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,100
I have no choice.

95
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:25,460
But I planted a bomb under the car.

96
00:07:27,070 --> 00:07:28,540
The second he opens the trunk,

97
00:07:28,940 --> 00:07:30,140
it'll blow him up.

98
00:07:30,620 --> 00:07:31,290
Say no more.

99
00:07:32,740 --> 00:07:33,340
I'll go.

100
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:37,370
I'll go.

101
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,100
I've been feeling

102
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:41,620
that something

103
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,580
is not right lately.

104
00:07:45,390 --> 00:07:46,170
I think

105
00:07:46,820 --> 00:07:47,780
your dad

106
00:07:48,060 --> 00:07:49,490
has run into some trouble.

107
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:52,050
I've never seen him like this before.

108
00:07:55,740 --> 00:07:57,020
I must be right.

109
00:07:57,380 --> 00:07:58,340
Something's happened to him.

110
00:07:59,300 --> 00:07:59,980
You know,

111
00:08:00,540 --> 00:08:02,540
I used to be a judge.

112
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,140
I've seen a lot.

113
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,050
Your father

114
00:08:07,510 --> 00:08:09,050
must be being threatened,

115
00:08:09,070 --> 00:08:10,340
even blackmailed, maybe.

116
00:08:11,190 --> 00:08:11,620
Yat-wai,

117
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,220
if you know anything at all,

118
00:08:14,420 --> 00:08:16,490
you have to tell me, okay?

119
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:19,900
I don't know.

120
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,730
Dad never tells me stuff like this.

121
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,580
Chi Cheung-wing is super paranoid.

122
00:08:31,510 --> 00:08:33,100
We can't let him know

123
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:34,700
you're replacing me.

124
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,890
Once you get there, notify me.

125
00:08:38,700 --> 00:08:40,530
I'll be the one to contact him.

126
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:41,650
Got it.

127
00:08:42,630 --> 00:08:43,650
I'll take you to the hospital

128
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:44,580
before I come back for the car.

129
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:46,700
I can't go to the hospital.

130
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:49,530
They'll tell right away
this is a gunshot wound.

131
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:52,220
If they take the bullet out
and run a match,

132
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,100
I'm a dead man.

133
00:08:55,150 --> 00:08:56,820
But the bullet's still in your body!

134
00:08:57,140 --> 00:08:58,100
If you don't go,

135
00:08:58,380 --> 00:08:59,020
you'll die too.

136
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,100
I'm not going.

137
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:04,180
Just go and drop the things over.

138
00:09:05,580 --> 00:09:07,130
You owe me this.

139
00:09:08,670 --> 00:09:10,220
No backing out.

140
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,530
Tell me what I should do.

141
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:19,300
Hey. What are you doing?

142
00:09:20,510 --> 00:09:21,940
This is not for killing

143
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,420
but self-protection.

144
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:39,940
Have you

145
00:09:40,550 --> 00:09:41,490
encountered anything

146
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:42,610
that looked

147
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,220
strange to you?

148
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,010
Like, strange calls

149
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:48,370
in the middle of the night,

150
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:51,010
or strange people spotted

151
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:53,060
around your home

152
00:09:53,260 --> 00:09:54,580
like they were watching you?

153
00:09:57,100 --> 00:09:57,850
No.

154
00:10:00,260 --> 00:10:00,650
No?

155
00:10:01,220 --> 00:10:01,860
No.

156
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:06,020
No,

157
00:10:06,860 --> 00:10:08,780
you must stay at my home for a few days

158
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:10,490
just in case.

159
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:11,820
That's not necessary.

160
00:10:12,140 --> 00:10:13,380
I don't see anything serious.

161
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:15,020
This isn't a negotiation.

162
00:10:16,340 --> 00:10:17,900
Go home and pack your clothes later.

163
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:19,140
You're moving to my place.

164
00:10:19,150 --> 00:10:20,010
But… my dad...

165
00:10:20,030 --> 00:10:20,730
Your dad?

166
00:10:20,910 --> 00:10:22,100
I'll explain it to him.

167
00:10:33,380 --> 00:10:34,180
Mr. Chun.

168
00:10:34,620 --> 00:10:35,530
You don't have to be scared.

169
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:37,610
I'm okay.

170
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:39,730
I'm not scared.

171
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:41,100
Don't fall asleep.

172
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,140
Keep talking to me.

173
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:43,890
Talk?

174
00:10:44,860 --> 00:10:46,060
About what?

175
00:10:49,740 --> 00:10:50,940
I just remembered

176
00:10:52,030 --> 00:10:54,220
we were classmates in elementary school.

177
00:10:56,380 --> 00:10:57,370
Actually, that day…

178
00:10:58,260 --> 00:10:59,980
did you recognize me back then?

179
00:11:00,630 --> 00:11:01,420
Your Honor.

180
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:03,730
[10 years ago]
As a police officer, the defendant

181
00:11:03,750 --> 00:11:06,010
should clearly understand
his responsibility to society,

182
00:11:06,390 --> 00:11:08,340
including protecting
the lives and property of citizens.

183
00:11:08,860 --> 00:11:10,250
However, he has violated the law
he is supposed to uphold

184
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:11,980
and even embezzled
the seized illegal money.

185
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,700
This act has utterly betrayed
the public's trust in civil servants.

186
00:11:15,220 --> 00:11:17,420
We urge Your Honor
to impose a severe penalty.

187
00:11:18,540 --> 00:11:19,940
I know I'm not a model police officer

188
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:22,340
who is incorruptible
and dedicated to duty.

189
00:11:23,460 --> 00:11:25,740
But I have never done anything

190
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:27,020
that harms people.

191
00:11:27,740 --> 00:11:29,140
The only reason they framed me together,

192
00:11:29,340 --> 00:11:30,260
claiming I was at the scene
and stole the money,

193
00:11:31,020 --> 00:11:32,500
is that I refused to play along

194
00:11:33,620 --> 00:11:34,860
and stood in the way

195
00:11:35,140 --> 00:11:36,020
of their profits.

196
00:11:36,620 --> 00:11:38,100
In this case, the defendant is accused

197
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:40,260
of violating the law
and stealing the seized illegal money

198
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:41,580
while performing his official duties.

199
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:44,370
Based on the evidence
presented in court so far:

200
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:45,220
First,

201
00:11:46,030 --> 00:11:47,530
there is no direct evidence

202
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:49,530
proving that the defendant
stole the seized illegal money.

203
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:50,940
Second,

204
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:52,730
there is equally
no direct evidence proving

205
00:11:53,260 --> 00:11:55,730
that the defendant placed
the seized illegal money in his vehicle.

206
00:11:57,140 --> 00:11:58,060
A court ruling

207
00:11:58,500 --> 00:11:59,650
is not based on one or two statements

208
00:12:00,020 --> 00:12:01,060
but is grounded in evidence.

209
00:12:01,380 --> 00:12:01,980
Therefore,

210
00:12:02,460 --> 00:12:03,490
It is so ordered

211
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:05,980
the existing evidence
is insufficient to confirm

212
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:07,340
the defendant's theft,

213
00:12:07,740 --> 00:12:08,770
and the defendant

214
00:12:08,780 --> 00:12:09,490
is acquitted of the charge.

215
00:12:21,390 --> 00:12:22,100
Mr. Chun,

216
00:12:22,660 --> 00:12:23,610
thank you for clearing my name.

217
00:12:24,380 --> 00:12:25,130
It's not me.

218
00:12:25,380 --> 00:12:27,100
What helped you
was the law and the evidence.

219
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:30,340
Do you really think
the outcome would be the same

220
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:32,770
if any other judge had heard this case?

221
00:12:34,780 --> 00:12:36,240
I don't have to go to jail
for something I didn't do,

222
00:12:37,140 --> 00:12:37,890
and I owe that to you.

223
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:41,010
From now on, stay on the right track.

224
00:12:43,510 --> 00:12:44,250
Thank you.

225
00:12:46,860 --> 00:12:47,650
Well, you...

226
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:48,700
You were often made
to repeat a year's course.

227
00:13:01,550 --> 00:13:02,850
Wai. Are you OK?

228
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:03,850
Wai.

229
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:05,370
Hey. Wai.

230
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:08,060
I...

231
00:13:10,390 --> 00:13:11,400
I'm alright.

232
00:13:13,620 --> 00:13:14,700
They ended

233
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:17,120
up dismissing me for misconduct,

234
00:13:19,220 --> 00:13:20,740
but because of you,

235
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:25,260
I didn't go to jail
for something I didn't do.

236
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:29,890
I still need to thank you.

237
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:31,700
I also know

238
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:34,100
that when some gangsters
harassed me later,

239
00:13:34,780 --> 00:13:36,580
you were the one who got me out
of the trouble secretly.

240
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:39,220
Repaying a favor to you, that's all.

241
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:42,530
Honestly, I'm pretty glad

242
00:13:44,860 --> 00:13:46,490
that we can be friends.

243
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:51,460
Having a judge as a friend?

244
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:54,180
That's quite a status.

245
00:13:58,140 --> 00:13:59,420
But your judge friend

246
00:14:00,460 --> 00:14:02,300
has been up to
a lot of shameful things lately.

247
00:14:03,060 --> 00:14:04,260
For your son,

248
00:14:06,260 --> 00:14:08,340
you've got to do that.

249
00:14:11,380 --> 00:14:12,060
Wai.

250
00:14:13,780 --> 00:14:14,490
Sorry.

251
00:14:15,860 --> 00:14:17,340
I never expected things
to turn this way.

252
00:14:19,220 --> 00:14:19,900
You know what?

253
00:14:21,660 --> 00:14:23,020
Without you,

254
00:14:25,220 --> 00:14:27,100
I would still be serving
my time in jail.

255
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,010
But you're also the reason

256
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:36,010
that I end up getting shot.

257
00:14:41,580 --> 00:14:43,260
Do you think I've gained more

258
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:46,700
or lost more?

259
00:14:48,420 --> 00:14:49,180
Don't collapse.

260
00:14:50,660 --> 00:14:51,370
When I come back,

261
00:14:51,780 --> 00:14:52,650
get this even with me,

262
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:53,850
okay?

263
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:55,530
Don't fall asleep.

264
00:15:21,980 --> 00:15:23,020
Your dad's home.

265
00:15:24,260 --> 00:15:25,220
He said he had plans for something.

266
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:26,380
Maybe he went without his car.

267
00:15:31,260 --> 00:15:32,500
Go up and pack your things.

268
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:33,780
I'll be waiting for you here.

269
00:16:46,140 --> 00:16:46,770
Madam,

270
00:16:48,020 --> 00:16:49,040
I've been suspended
for almost a month and a half.

271
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:51,420
C&IIB called me in for questioning,

272
00:16:51,580 --> 00:16:52,610
but there's no conclusion.

273
00:16:53,060 --> 00:16:54,610
They said whether I can get reinstated
depends on you.

274
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:56,820
Actually, it should be

275
00:16:57,140 --> 00:16:58,250
whether you can get reinstated

276
00:16:58,820 --> 00:16:59,890
depends on yourself.

277
00:17:01,740 --> 00:17:03,530
Madam, I've told you this many times.

278
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:05,000
Even though I'm from the old town,

279
00:17:05,270 --> 00:17:06,940
I'm also a cop.

280
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:10,160
Madam,

281
00:17:11,060 --> 00:17:11,980
I have a tip about Chi Cheung-wing.

282
00:17:17,380 --> 00:17:19,420
They say Hon Lit dared to kill people
in the old town.

283
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:21,320
That's a direct provocation
to the old town gang.

284
00:17:22,900 --> 00:17:24,300
Can you tell me something
I don't already know?

285
00:17:25,860 --> 00:17:27,960
Chi Cheung-wing's men
are handling a batch of arms.

286
00:17:28,460 --> 00:17:30,380
